### Restrictions

```
ojp:Type
```

There are the following types:
- stop
- address
- poi
- coord
- topographicPlace
The main uses are stop and coord. poi will become more important over time (particularly for car parks and sharers).
Sharing vehicles (e-scooters, bicycles, cars) and charging stations can now be accessed as POI (see ojp:PointOfInterestFilter below).
For address, you first have to use general input to determine the exact LocationName. You then have to use this name and the type ‘address’. Only then does the address code come back. However, this is a special case and should not normally be used. Neither address code nor TopographicPlaceRef have any meaning outside of OJP searches.

```
<ojp:Type>stop</ojp:Type>
```


```
ojp:Usage
```

There are the following values:
- origin
- via
- destination
The feature is not supported.

