The result is sorted in descending order by probability (most relevant first).
The selection of the best candidates for the hit list is determined after the input text matches the entire data set. The probability is determined based on the number of matching trigrams into which the terms can be broken down and the remainder that does not match. If there is a complete match, i.e. no remainder, there is a full match and the candidate receives the maximum probability 1. If there is still a remainder, points are deducted. The hits thus found can then be influenced by means of various evaluation criteria, quality and sorting order. The results can be changed based on the region (municipality code), type (stop, address, town, POI,…), the serving means of transport or a relevance value.

